Title:          mhWaveEdit.tcz
Description:    A simple GTK2 sound editor and converter
Version:        1.4.15
Author:         Magnus Hjorth
Original-site:  https://gna.org/projects/mhwaveedit
Copying-policy: GPLv2
Size:           276K
Extension_by:   perthie
Tags:	    GTK2 sound editor converter
Comments:       Requires gtk2.tcz, libasound.tcz, libsamplerate.tcz, 
                libsndfile.tcz, flac.tcz, ogg-vorbis.tcz, lame.tcz
                -------------
                Go to Edit > Preferences > Sound and select your driver (OSS or ALSA).
                Go to Edit > Preferences > Other and set your mixer (ossxmix or alsamixer).
                Run in a full-width window to see all the controls.
                Use a right-click to position the cursor on the track.
                Recording may not work with OSS. Instead use: ossrecord filename.wav
                Check the folder ~/.mhwaveedit for occasional large left-over files.
